Bath beat London Irish 26-13 at the Rec in the Aviva Premiership . 
  Sam Burgess was man-of-the-match for the home side . 
  George Ford kicked five penalties for the hosts . 
  Leroy Houston, Jonathan Joseph, Matt Banahan and Semesa Rokoduguni scored tries for Bath . 
  London Irish loosehead Tom Court scored a try for the visitors . 
 